						<summary>

						<p>On a stone lying in a garden near the Karanam's house.</p>						

						<p>Eastern Gaṅga: Chōḍagaṅgadēva, 63rd year.</p>						

						<p>This is dated Śaka 1059, Siṁha, ba. 14 Wednesday.</p>						

						<p>Records the gift of money for burning a perpetual lamp in the temple of Karaṁjīśvara at Ippili by a certain Rēvi-Nāyaka, son of Kommana-Nāyaka and Eṟakama-Nāyakuṟālu. The donor gets the titles of <hi rend="italic">Śrīkaraṇa</hi> and • • • • • <hi rend="italic">vidhyādhara.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
